inking=\r\n in case I am going down the wrong path. I have been doing the Ganapathi Ho=\r\nmam for the past half a year or so and I should say that I am not maintaini=\r\nng the Brahmacharya as &quot;defined&quot; in the mail exchanges and some books. I fe=\r\nel that the problem with Sex with most of us is that we tend to identify it=\r\n with something wrong or something which is &quot;impure&quot; and hence forbidden. I=\r\n have been performing some experiments in my daily life and I have found th=\r\nat it is defintitely possible to avoid the feelings of Lust, Greed and othe=\r\nr feelings even while having sex. Although I am not perfect in this but I f=\r\neel with lot of practice it should=C2=A0be possible to achieve a state of m=\r\nind even during sex where you are focussed on=C2=A0God and not wavered by t=\r\nhe feelings that accompanies mundane sex. In this\n case even something as m=\r\naterialistic as Sex will be transformed into a=C2=A0intense spiritual sadha=\r\nna.=C2=A0If you start thinking of Sex not as sometihng Impure and start doi=\r\nng it as Karma itself with out any other accompanying thoughts and do the &quot;=\r\nAct&quot; itself as an offering to God then I feel that Brahmacharya as defined =\r\nconventionally is not needed. I would say that we are very much observing B=\r\nrahmacharya. Now coming to Ojas I doubt that Ojas can be so physical as Sem=\r\nen. If the act of Sex is itself perfomed as an offering to God and without =\r\nany thoughts other than that of God then where is the question of loosing a=\r\nny spiritual energy . In fact you are adding to your spiritual growth. \nI h=\r\nave observed a change in myself after doing this practically over the past =\r\ncouple of months. I have found that gradually over a period of time even th=\r\nough its possible to completely abstain from physical sex, it is also possi=\r\nble to avoid getting swayed by it and also not crave for it.\n=C2=A0\nContinu=\r\ning further=C2=A0, how would one justify &quot;Nightfalls&quot; which is a natural ph=\r\nenomenon wherein the body automatically purges excess semen collected over =\r\na period of time when one is asleep without the persons control.In other wo=\r\nrds it is an involuntary=C2=A0action just like breathing.\n\nCan this also be=\r\n=C2=A0intrepreted as break in Brahmacharya? I would be keen to know the exp=\r\neriences of those persons who have abstained from physical sex for an exten=\r\nded period of time and=C2=A0what they think=C2=A0of=C2=A0&quot;Nightfalls&quot;.\n\n***=\r\n***************************************************************************=\r\n**************************************************\n\nI think that every acti=\r\non that we do should be done with the thought of an offering to god. For ex=\r\nample even while having food , we can think each bite as an offering to Gan=\r\napathi in fire (actually there is a fire in our stomach which burns the foo=\r\nd) , Our entire body can be visuilased like a living moving Homa kundam whe=\r\nre we continuously offer ahuti of differnet materials. If we conciously mak=\r\ne this effort over a period of time we would think less about the process o=\r\nf eating=C2=A0food itself , the accompanying pleasure of taste etc and conc=\r\nentrate more on mental homam which we are performing. Every thought process=\r\n can be considered as an ahuti inside the mental fire in our soul.Like this=\r\n every action that we do in our daily life can be thought as a homam itself=\r\n and thereby achieve the state of mind where there is no distinction betwee=\r\nn the so called &quot;Pure&quot; and &quot;Impure&quot; , &quot;Good&quot; and &quot;Bad&quot; and so on.\n\nPlease l=\r\net us=C2=A0know your thoughts on this. If possible try to get Manishji&#39;s op=\r\ninion on this as well.\n\nThanks and Regards,\nGirish Sundaram\n\n\n\n\n___________=\r\n_____________________\nFrom: Narasimha PVR Rao &lt;pvr@...&gt;\nTo: vedic-w=\r\nisdom@yahoogroups.com\nSent: Wed, March 3, 2010 5:03:20 AM\nSubject: [vedic-w=\r\nisdom] Brahmacharya (Re: Regarding Ganapati Homam...)\n\n=C2=A0 \nNamaste Bisw=\r\najit,\n\nGood luck with homam. Others answered your questions and I will leav=\r\ne them. But I want to say a few words on (3) as the recent discussion on ag=\r\nhora seems to have created some confusion. It is very easy to misunderstand=\r\n when we are communicating verbally, because one&#39;s own mental conditioning =\r\nhas a role in deciding how one interprets words, sentences and their sub-te=\r\nxt. It is more so when we are talking about delicate matters.\n\n* * *\n\n&gt; 3. =\r\nWhen the talking of &quot;AGHORA&quot; going on, is it really needed\n&gt; to perform &quot;Br=\r\namhachariya&quot; for daily ganapati homam?\n\nBrahmacharya is very important in a=\r\nny spiritual sadhana. Period. As Narayan said, sexual activity results in l=\r\noss of ojas (subtle vitality) and wastes a part of one&#39;s creative essence. =\r\nDoing sadhana without brahmacharya is like filling a water pot that is leak=\r\ning through a hole. Even if you succeed in filling the pot with water, it w=\r\nill soon become empty!\n\nJust as a filled water pot that is leaking may stil=\r\nl satisfy the thirst of someone who takes a glass of water from it, similar=\r\nly a person doing sadhana without brahmacharya may sometimes be able to do =\r\nhis dharma and serve his purpose in the world. So, it is a good idea to do =\r\nsadhana even as one&#39;s brahmacharya is not good yet. But, the best will be i=\r\nf the filled water pot is not leaking and holds all the water. Similarly, a=\r\n sadhaka who is accumulating some shakti through sadhana and does not leak =\r\nthat energy through acts of lust, anger, greed, jealosy etc will be able to=\r\n serve dharma better.\n\nIf there are 12 people who maintain physical and men=\r\ntal brahmacharya for a few years while doing homam everyday, I think the wo=\r\nrld can be changed.\n\n* * *\n\nIf an aghora sits naked with partner and chants=\r\n mantra, please remember that the goal isn&#39;t having sex. This practice is b=\r\ny means a glorification of sex. The goal is to *resist*. Even if the mind i=\r\ns overwhelmed in the beginning with thrill and one ends up having sex, the =\r\ngoal is to reach a stage where mind is not looking at nakedness or intimacy=\r\n as something to be excited about. The goal is to reach a stage where brahm=\r\nacharya can be maintained despite such provocation.\n\nIn fact, the true mean=\r\ning of brahmacharya is not only to refrain from physical sex but also to re=\r\nfrain from sexual thoughts in the mind. Many married people of today may be=\r\n able to set time limits (e.g. 40 days, 100 days, 1 year etc) and maintain =\r\nphysical brahmacharya for that time, but it may be difficult to refrain fro=\r\nm mental thoughts.\n\nAn aghora tries to incinerate the root cause of those t=\r\nhoughts in his mind (what Manish called as &quot;sampradaaha&quot; ). Mind considers =\r\nsome things as pure and some things as impure. The &quot;impure&quot; objects and cir=\r\ncumstances are considered impure because they cause thrill or some other di=\r\nsturbance to the mind and waver it from god. But an aghora puts them right =\r\nin the middle of a &quot;pure&quot; activity (e.g. meditation), forcing oneself to de=\r\nal with them. After some time, the impure objects do not cause any thrill o=\r\nr other disturbance to waver the mind from god. Then they are no longer imp=\r\nure! For example, what is impure about a naked body? The only thing impure =\r\nabout it is that it arouses certain thoughts in mind that disturb the mind =\r\nand waver it from god. If a naked body no longer arouses such thoughts, wha=\r\nt is impure about it?\n\nThat is the basic thinking in this practice. Some yo=\r\ngis may physically abstain from sex and even stay away from exposure to opp=\r\nosite sex, for several decades. But, if such a person is placed in front of=\r\n a naked beauty, what thoughts will go on his mind? For all you know, his m=\r\nind may indeed be disturbed and waver from god. An aghora tries to incinera=\r\nte the very notion in the mind that so and so thing is something to be arou=\r\nsed by, not by staying away from it but by being with it and yet trying to =\r\nfocus the mind on god.\n\nBottomline: An aghora engaging in this practice may=\r\n stray from brahmacharya in the beginning, but the goal is to attain more p=\r\nerfect brahmacharya later on. The goal of this practice is to attain brahma=\r\ncharya.\n\nIf one does not keep brahmacharya in the beginning of sadhana, it =\r\nmay be ok. But, to really start progressing, one needs to somehow or the ot=\r\nher attain some level of brahmacharya and keep perfecting it.\n\n* * *\n\nThe c=\r\noarse meaning of brahmacharya is physical celibacy.\n\nThe finer meaning of b=\r\nrahmacharya is physical celibacy and refraining from any sexual thoughts ev=\r\nen in the mind.\n\nThe finest meaning of brahmacharya is refraining from lust=\r\n, anger, greed, delusion, wantonness and jealosy and establishing mind in B=\r\nrahman always. Brahmacharya literally means &quot;engaging in Brahman or Self&quot;. =\r\nOne experiences lust, anger, greed, jealosy etc only when one&#39;s mind percei=\r\nves and engages with impermanent manifestations of Self (e.g. a beautiful l=\r\nady, a bad person, a lot of money, a person being appreciated more than me =\r\netc) and NOT when one&#39;s mind engages in true Self. Thus the truest brahmach=\r\narya comes only on Self-realization. But one can start with physical celiba=\r\ncy and control over anger.\n\nRome is not built in a day.\n\nBottomline: It is =\r\nvery important to keep brahmacharya, even using the coarse meaning above. S=\r\ntart off with some level of brahmacharya and try to improve it as time goes=\r\n on. Never be frustrated with lack of progress and keep trying.\n\n* * *\n\nBTW=\r\n, regarding (4), even after fire goes away, you can meditate. Fire will be =\r\nburning in the ember form for a long time. So Agni is still there consuming=\r\n your offerings, even after it seems like there is no fire.\n\nKeep it as che=\r\nap as you can, based on your financial level. Little ghee, fallen wood stic=\r\nks collected manually and some sesame seeds may be all you need.\n\nBest rega=\r\nrds,\nNarasimha\n------------ --------- --------- --------- --------- -------=\r\n-- -\nFree Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyotish Writings,\n&quot;Do It =\r\nYourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam and Pitri Tarpana:\nhttp://www.Vedi=\r\ncAst rologer.org\nFilms that make a difference: http://SaraswatiFil ms.org\nS=\r\npirituality: http://groups. yahoo.com/ group/vedic- wisdom\nJyotish writings=\r\n: http://groups. yahoo.com/ group/JyotishWri tings\n------------ --------- -=\r\n-------- --------- --------- --------- -\n\n---- biswa108 &lt;biswa1975@yahoo. c=\r\nom&gt; wrote: \n&gt; NAMASKAR to all\n&gt; \n&gt; I have been performing Ganapati Homama f=\r\nor the last three weeks, credit goes to all of my seniors/members and Gurus=\r\n of this beautiful forum...\n&gt; \n&gt; Now I need some practical approach best su=\r\nitable for me...\n&gt; \n&gt; 1. Suggested / Suitable time to perform ganapati homa=\r\nm(currently, I am performing around the time of sunrise, is it suitable at =\r\nnight or before sunrise too?)\n&gt; \n&gt; 2. What substance should not be offered =\r\nin Ganapati homam (bel-leaves should be one in the list, I unknowingly used=\r\n it and experience very bad effects!) \n&gt; \n&gt; 3. When the talking of &quot;AGHORA&quot;=\r\n going on, is it really needed to perform &quot;Bramhachariya&quot; for daily ganapat=\r\ni homam? if someone can control his/her thinkings during ganapati homam, se=\r\nx/masturbating/ consume non-veg food is really needed? (In my practical exp=\r\nerience, consume very low-diet little food at last night are excellent for =\r\nperforming Ganapati Homama in the morning.