e to do his dharma and serve his purpose =\r\nin the world. So, it is a good idea to do sadhana even as one&#39;s brahmachary=\r\na is not good yet. But, the best will be if the filled water pot is not lea=\r\nking and holds all the water. Similarly, a sadhaka who is accumulating some=\r\n shakti through sadhana and does not leak that energy through acts of lust,=\r\n anger, greed, jealosy etc will be able to serve dharma better.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;If t=\r\nhere are 12 people who maintain physical and mental brahmacharya for a few =\r\nyears while doing homam everyday, I think the world can be changed.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;=\r\n* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;If an aghora sits naked with partner and chants mantra, please=\r\n remember that the goal isn&#39;t having sex. This practice is by means a glori=\r\nfication of sex. The goal is to *resist*.\n Even if the mind is overwhelmed =\r\nin the beginning with thrill and one ends up having sex, the goal is to rea=\r\nch a stage where mind is not looking at nakedness or intimacy as something =\r\nto be excited about. The goal is to reach a stage where brahmacharya can be=\r\n maintained despite such provocation.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In fact, the true meaning of b=\r\nrahmacharya is not only to refrain from physical sex but also to refrain fr=\r\nom sexual thoughts in the mind. Many married people of today may be able to=\r\n set time limits (e.g. 40 days, 100 days, 1 year etc) and maintain physical=\r\n brahmacharya for that time, but it may be difficult to refrain from mental=\r\n thoughts.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;An aghora tries to incinerate the root cause of those tho=\r\nughts in his mind (what Manish called as &quot;sampradaaha&quot; ). Mind considers so=\r\nme things as pure and some things as impure. The &quot;impure&quot; objects and circu=\r\nmstances are considered impure because they cause thrill or some other dist=\r\nurbance to the mind and waver it\n from god. But an aghora puts them right i=\r\nn the middle of a &quot;pure&quot; activity (e.g. meditation), forcing oneself to dea=\r\nl with them. After some time, the impure objects do not cause any thrill or=\r\n other disturbance to waver the mind from god. Then they are no longer impu=\r\nre! For example, what is impure about a naked body? The only thing impure a=\r\nbout it is that it arouses certain thoughts in mind that disturb the mind a=\r\nnd waver it from god. If a naked body no longer arouses such thoughts, what=\r\n is impure about it?&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;That is the basic thinking in this practice. So=\r\nme yogis may physically abstain from sex and even stay away from exposure t=\r\no opposite sex, for several decades. But, if such a person is placed in fro=\r\nnt of a naked beauty, what thoughts will go on his mind? For all you know, =\r\nhis mind may indeed be disturbed and waver from god. An aghora tries to inc=\r\ninerate the very notion in the mind that so and so thing is something to be=\r\n aroused by, not by\n staying away from it but by being with it and yet tryi=\r\nng to focus the mind on god.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Bottomline: An aghora engaging in this =\r\npractice may stray from brahmacharya in the beginning, but the goal is to a=\r\nttain more perfect brahmacharya later on. The goal of this practice is to a=\r\nttain brahmacharya.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;If one does not keep brahmacharya in the beginni=\r\nng of sadhana, it may be ok. But, to really start progressing, one needs to=\r\n somehow or the other attain some level of brahmacharya and keep perfecting=\r\n it.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;The coarse meaning of brahmacharya is physical cel=\r\nibacy.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;The finer meaning of brahmacharya is physical celibacy and re=\r\nfraining from any sexual thoughts even in the mind.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;The finest meani=\r\nng of brahmacharya is refraining from lust, anger, greed, delusion, wantonn=\r\ness and jealosy and establishing mind in Brahman always. Brahmacharya liter=\r\nally means &quot;engaging in Brahman or Self&quot;. One experiences lust, anger, gree=\r\nd, jealosy\n etc only when one&#39;s mind perceives and engages with impermanent=\r\n manifestations of Self (e.g. a beautiful lady, a bad person, a lot of mone=\r\ny, a person being appreciated more than me etc) and NOT when one&#39;s mind eng=\r\nages in true Self. Thus the truest brahmacharya comes only on Self-realizat=\r\nion. But one can start with physical celibacy and control over anger.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;B=\r\nR&gt;Rome is not built in a day.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Bottomline: It is very important to ke=\r\nep brahmacharya, even using the coarse meaning above. Start off with some l=\r\nevel of brahmacharya and try to improve it as time goes on. Never be frustr=\r\nated with lack of progress and keep trying.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;BTW, regard=\r\ning (4), even after fire goes away, you can meditate. Fire will be burning =\r\nin the ember form for a long time. So Agni is still there consuming your of=\r\nferings, even after it seems like there is no fire.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Keep it as cheap=\r\n as you can, based on your financial level. Little ghee, fallen wood sticks=\r\n\n collected manually and some sesame seeds may be all you need.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Best=\r\n regards,&lt;BR&gt;Narasimha&lt;BR&gt;------------ --------- --------- --------- ------=\r\n--- --------- -&lt;BR&gt;Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyotish Wri=\r\ntings,&lt;BR&gt;&quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam and Pitri Tarpana=\r\n:&lt;BR&gt;&lt;A href=3D&quot;http://www.vedicastrologer.org/&quot; target=3D_blank rel=3Dnofo=\r\nllow&gt;http://www.VedicAst rologer.org&lt;/A&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Films that make a difference: &lt;=\r\nA href=3D&quot;http://saraswatifilms.org/&quot; target=3D_blank rel=3Dnofollow&gt;http:/=\r\n/SaraswatiFil ms.org&lt;/A&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Spirituality: &lt;A href=3D&quot;http://groups.yahoo.co=\r\nm/group/vedic-wisdom&quot; target=3D_blank rel=3Dnofo